#frontpage
  %p
    %em
      Aeolus is an umbrella project for many pieces of cloud software.

    %br
    The showpiece of Aeolus is the Aeolus Conductor, a web UI in front of the
    <a href="http://www.deltacloud.org">Deltacloud</a> API.  With Aeolus Conductor, your users can:
    %ul
      %li
        View image status and stats across clouds, all in one place
      %li
        Manage images locally and provision them on any cloud
  %p
    :markdown
      If you are new to Aeolus, please see the [Getting Started][start] page.

      [start]: getting_started.html

  %p
    %em
      The full list of projects hosted here are:
    %ul
      %li
        = link_to 'Conductor', 'conductor.html'
        &ndash; multiple cloud web UI
      %li
        = link_to 'Oz', 'oz.html'
        &ndash; automated virtual machine installer
      %li
        = link_to 'Image Factory', 'imagefactory.html'
        &ndash; daemon with a QMF interface for building cloud images
      %li
        = link_to 'Image Warehouse', 'imagewarehouse.html'
        &ndash; a daemon to move cloud images from cloud to cloud
        based on rules
      %li
        = link_to 'Audrey', 'audrey.html'
        &ndash; a set of tools to do run-time configuration of cloud instances
  %p
    The Aeolus Project is free and open source (LGPL, GPL).
